Valynt Value Orchestration: Master Architecture v2.0Executive SummaryValynt is a production-grade system for bridging the gap between strategic value claims and realized business outcomes. This document establishes the Valynt Value Model, a unified orchestration framework that prioritizes deterministic financial integrity and "Truthful Telemetry" over speculative AI generation.1. Layer 1: Canonical Ontology & InvariantsThe following 7 entities constitute the irreducible core of the Valynt system. To ensure audit-grade lineage, these entities utilize bitemporal tracking (System Time vs. Effective Business Time).1.1 Core EntitiesAccount: The legal entity (Customer).Opportunity: The specific engagement or value-creation initiative.ValueHypothesis: A testable claim regarding an economic driver.BusinessCase: A versioned, frozen container of validated hypotheses.Assumption: An auditable input variable (Benchmark, Customer Stated, or Calculated).ValueCommitment: A contractual promise derived from a BusinessCase.RealizationProof: Verifiable telemetry (Actual vs. Committed).1.2 Temporal & Audit InvariantsFrozen Context: Once a BusinessCase moves to presented or approved, its linked Assumptions and Hypotheses are snapshotted.Bitemporal Fields: All assumptions and proofs must track:valid_from / valid_to: When the value is true in the business world.recorded_at: When the system registered the data.Deterministic Boundary: AI agents may propose schemas or narratives, but the Economic Kernel (defined in Layer 3) is the sole authority for financial arithmetic.2. Layer 2: The Claim Maturity ModelThe backbone of Valynt is the transition of value claims through four distinct maturity states.Maturity StateDefinitionIntegrity RequirementSpeculativeInitial AI-generated hypothesis.Silver-tier evidence; Agent-generated.ValidatedHuman-reviewed; passes integrity gates.Gold/Platinum evidence; $S_{DR} \ge 0.8$.CommittedContractually "frozen" in a Business Case.Explicit stakeholder approval; System-locked.ProvenRealized via external telemetry.Platinum evidence; Variance analysis complete.2.1 Transition RulesSpeculative → Validated: Requires a human_reviewed flag on all linked Assumptions and an IntegrityAgent score $\ge 0.6$.Validated → Committed: Requires the generation of a BusinessCase version and a transition of the Opportunity to closed_won.Committed → Proven: Requires a RealizationProof linked to a ValueCommitment with a documented telemetry source.3. Layer 3: Execution Architecture3.1 The Economic KernelTo eliminate LLM hallucination in finance, all math is executed by the Economic Kernel using Decimal.js.Inputs: Validated Assumptions and Hypothesis structures.Outputs: Deterministic NPV, IRR, ROI, and Payback Period.Sensitivity: Automatic generation of Conservative (P10), Base (P50), and Upside (P90) scenarios.3.2 Agent Fabric (Consolidated Core 5)DiscoveryAgent: Scans account context and EDGAR/Benchmarks to generate Speculative hypotheses.ModelingAgent: Maps hypotheses to the Economic Kernel and manages Assumption sensitivity.IntegrityAgent: The "Veto Gate." Evaluates evidence tiers and computes the Integrity Score.CommitmentAgent: Translates models into contractual KPIs and milestones.RealizationAgent: Monitors telemetry (Salesforce, ERP) to generate RealizationProofs.3.3 Salesforce RLM Integration HookAs a primary enterprise integration, Valynt connects to Salesforce Revenue Lifecycle Management (RLM):Product Discovery: Inject Valynt "Value Templates" into the RLM Product Browsing API.Asset Actions: The RealizationAgent monitors AssetAction records (Upsells/Downsells) as primary telemetry for value realization.Fulfillment DRO: Track FulfillmentStep completion to calculate "Time-to-Value."4. Layer 4: Governance & Scoring PolicyValynt utilizes governance heuristics to gate the value lifecycle. These are policy choices intended for calibration over time.4.1 Defense Readiness Score ($S_{DR}$)Measures the auditability of the data.$$S_{DR} = 0.6 \cdot \left( \frac{\sum A_{validated}}{\sum A_{total}} \right) + 0.4 \cdot \overline{G}_{evidence}$$$A_{validated}$: Count of human-reviewed assumptions.$\overline{G}_{evidence}$: Mean grounding score from secureInvoke.4.2 Integrity Score ($S_{I}$)The final gate for external presentation.$$S_{I} = \text{clamp} \left[ 0.5 \cdot S_{DR} + 0.5 \cdot (1 - \sum V_{penalties}), 0, 1 \right]$$Critical Violation (-0.20): E.g., No evidence for a high-value claim.Dismissed Critical (-0.05): Transparency penalty for overridden warnings.5. Layer 5: Current-State Audit & Migration Plan5.1 Honest Gap AssessmentCapabilityTarget StateCurrent RealityStatusFinancial ModelingDeterministic KernelHardcoded ModelStageMockedIntegrity VetoLogic-based gateUI-only queue; Stage disconnectedMockedNarrative GenNarrativeAgent PDFExport panel non-functionalMissingCRM SyncBi-directional RLMDecorative integrations pageMocked5.2 Migration RoadmapPhase 1 (Immediate): Wire Dashboard "Go" button; implement basic NarrativeAgent.Phase 2 (2-4 Weeks): Integrate Decimal.js Kernel; implement IntegrityAgent Veto Gate logic.Phase 3 (4-8 Weeks): Bi-directional Salesforce RLM sync; Bitemporal schema migration.6. Layer 6: Market Differentiation & PositioningValynt is defined by three unrivaled capabilities:Truthful Telemetry: We don't just "calculate" ROI; we track it against actual system-of-record telemetry.Economic Kernel: We treat value engineering as an audit-grade financial process, not a creative writing exercise.Integrity-First Flow: Our "Veto Gate" ensures that no unvalidated claim reaches a customer, protecting the brand equity of the sales organization.
